The '''Nightingale Island finch''' ('''''Nesospiza questi''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Thraupidae]] (formerly in [[Emberizidae]]).

It is [[endemic]] to [[Nightingale Island]] of the [[Tristan da Cunha]] [[archipelago]], where its natural [[habitat]]s are temperate [[shrubland]] and subantarctic [[grassland]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

